        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-05-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <head>No. 797.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beardsley</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Agency and Consulate-General of the United States in
                                            Egypt</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-05-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 30,
                                    1874</date>. (Received June 30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 201.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that,
                                by circular from the ministry of foreign affairs, dated the 27th
                                instant, the entire question of judicial reform has been placed in
                                charge of Cherif Pasha, minister of justice, to whom all
                                communications in the future will be addressed, instead of to the
                                minister of foreign affairs as hitherto.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. BEARDSLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
